the U.S. Agriculture Department isproposing to permit coverage of freight cost and marine and warrisk insurance for sales  of all agricultural commodities soldon credit terms under the Commodity Credit Corporation's, CCC,credit guarantee programs.    The proposal only applies to commodities that are sold byexporters on a cost and freight, C and F, or cost, insuranceand freight, CIF, basis, since these costs would be included inthe exporter's sale price to the foreign buyer, it said.    Under current programs, freight costs can be covered onlyfor export sales of U.S. breeding animals.    It asked for comments on the proposal by April 20. Reuter&#3;